\title{atcddd: WHO ATC/DDD Crawler and Parser}
\description{
Crawl, parse, search, and compute with the World Health Organization's
Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) classification system and Defined
Daily Dose (DDD) Index. This package provides a complete toolkit for
pharmacoepidemiology, drug utilisation research, and clinical data
science.

\strong{The package ships with no WHO data.} Use \code{\link[=atc_download]{atc_download()}} to retrieve
the current ATC/DDD Index from the WHO Collaborating Centre. Data are
cached locally for offline use across sessions.
}
\section{Main Features}{

\itemize{
\item \strong{Data Download}: \code{\link[=atc_download]{atc_download()}} retrieves the WHO index
to your local user-cache directory for persistent offline use.
\item \strong{Web Crawling}: \code{\link[=atc_crawl]{atc_crawl()}} for low-level iterative
traversal of the ATC hierarchy with configurable rate limiting.
\item \strong{Drug Name Search}: \code{\link[=search_drug]{search_drug()}}, \code{\link[=fuzzy_match_drug]{fuzzy_match_drug()}},
and \code{\link[=resolve_atc]{resolve_atc()}} for offline drug-name-to-ATC-code resolution
with brand-name synonyms and typo-tolerant matching.
\item \strong{Clinical Text Extraction}: \code{\link[=atc_from_text]{atc_from_text()}} extracts
drug names from free-text clinical notes.
\item \strong{DDD Computation}: \code{\link[=compute_ddd]{compute_ddd()}} and \code{\link[=compute_did]{compute_did()}}
convert prescription data into Defined Daily Doses and DDDs per
1000 inhabitants per day.
\item \strong{Hierarchy Navigation}: \code{\link[=atc_children]{atc_children()}},
\code{\link[=atc_descendants]{atc_descendants()}}, \code{\link[=atc_parent]{atc_parent()}}, and \code{\link[=atc_level]{atc_level()}} for
exploring the five-level ATC classification tree.
\item \strong{Reproducibility}: \code{\link[=atc_manifest]{atc_manifest()}} generates SHA256
checksums for downloaded data files.
}
